#: ../../../reference/generated/numpy.remainder.rst:4
msgid "numpy.remainder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:2
msgid "Returns the element-wise remainder of division."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:4
msgid ""
"Computes the remainder complementary to the `floor_divide` function.  It is "
"equivalent to the Python modulus operator ``x1 % x2`` and has the same sign "
"as the divisor `x2`. The MATLAB function equivalent to ``np.remainder`` is "
"``mod``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:11
msgid "This should not be confused with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:13
msgid ""
"Python's `math.remainder` and C's ``remainder``, which compute the IEEE "
"remainder, which are the complement to ``round(x1 / x2)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:16
msgid ""
"The MATLAB ``rem`` function and or the C ``%`` operator which is the "
"complement to ``int(x1 / x2)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:22
msgid "**x1**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:-1
msgid "array_like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:22
msgid "Dividend array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:27
msgid "**x2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:25
msgid ""
"Divisor array. If ``x1.shape != x2.shape``, they must be broadcastable to a "
"common shape (which becomes the shape of the output)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:33
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:-1
msgid "ndarray, None, or tuple of ndarray and None, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:30
msgid ""
"A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have a "
"shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or None, a freshly-"
"allocated array is returned. A tuple (possible only as a keyword argument) "
"must have length equal to the number of outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:41
msgid "**where**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:-1
msgid "array_like, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:36
msgid ""
"This condition is broadcast over the input. At locations where the condition "
"is True, the `out` array will be set to the ufunc result. Elsewhere, the "
"`out` array will retain its original value. Note that if an uninitialized "
"`out` array is created via the default ``out=None``, locations within it "
"where the condition is False will remain uninitialized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:47
msgid "**\\*\\*kwargs**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:44
msgid ""
"For other keyword-only arguments, see the :ref:`ufunc docs <ufuncs.kwargs>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:59
msgid "**y**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:-1
msgid "ndarray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:52
msgid ""
"The element-wise remainder of the quotient ``floor_divide(x1, x2)``. This is "
"a scalar if both `x1` and `x2` are scalars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:64
msgid ":obj:`floor_divide`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:65
msgid "Equivalent of Python ``//`` operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:66
msgid ":obj:`divmod`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:67
msgid "Simultaneous floor division and remainder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:68
msgid ":obj:`fmod`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:69
msgid "Equivalent of the MATLAB ``rem`` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:70
msgid ":obj:`divide`, :obj:`floor`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:74
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:75
msgid ""
"Returns 0 when `x2` is 0 and both `x1` and `x2` are (arrays of) integers. "
"``mod`` is an alias of ``remainder``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:81
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.remainder:92
msgid ""
"The ``%`` operator can be used as a shorthand for ``np.remainder`` on "
"ndarrays."
msgstr ""

